Since we're not pivoting, for `K+1` classes problem, `count_0` should not be in formula. 

``` latex
             {{{
               P(0) = \exp(b_0) / (\sum_{k=0}^K \exp(b_k))
               ...
               P(K) = \exp(b_K) / (\sum_{k=0}^K \exp(b_k))
             }}}
```

we have a freedom to chose the phase `lambda` since the solution isn't identifiable, so

``` latex
             {{{
               b_k = \log{count_k + 1} + \lambda    for all k in {0, K}  
               ( +1 is for smoothing for the classes that zero count so this is applied even histogram(i) == 0)
             }}}
```

we can chose `\lambda  = - \mean{b_k}` as you suggest to minimize L1 and L2 loss together.

This can not be a sparse vector once the `interceptVector` is centered. 

``` scala
val interceptVector = if (intercepts.length > 1) {
  val interceptMean = intercepts.sum / intercepts.length
  for (i = 0 until i < intercepts.length) {
    intercepts(i) -= interceptMean
  }
} else {
  Vectors.sparse(numClasses, Seq())
}
```
